Step 4: To check, I can multiply the quotient by the divisor and add the remainder, and see if I get back the original polynomial:

\begin{align*}
(3x^3 + 4x^2 + 4x + 1)(2x - 6) + (-140) &= 6x^4 - 18x^3 + 8x^3 - 24x^2 + 8x^2 - 24x + 2x - 6 + (-140) \\
&= 6x^4 - 14x^3 - 4x^2 + 2x - 26
\end{align*}
